    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In the Mexican presidential election on Sunday (front page, July 3), the ruling party's candidate had to fight not only the other candidates  but also the weight of 71 years of history.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In the Mexican presidential election on Sunday (front page, July 3), the ruling party's candidate had to fight not only the other candidates  but also the weight of 71 years of history.</p>
        <p>In the end, the people of Mexico have won for themselves the liberty of chastising the parties that are not doing their job well, and that is a wonderful thing to have.</p>
        <p>ROBERTO C. GARZA  Pharr, Tex., July 3, 2000</p>
      </block>
